🔐 SECURITY CHECKLIST

  Before deploying to production:

  ☐ Rotate all Supabase keys (Settings → API → Rotate)
  ☐ Use separate Nvidia API keys for creative vs analytical models
  ☐ Add .env to .gitignore (already done)
  ☐ Use AWS Secrets Manager or similar for production
  ☐ Never log API keys to stdout/stderr
  ☐ Implement API rate limiting on frontend (max 5 requests/min per user)
  ☐ Monitor Nvidia API usage for unexpected spikes


═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

✅ QUICK START

  1. Get Nvidia API keys from https://build.nvidia.com/
  2. Edit .env and replace placeholders:
     - NVIDIA_API_KEY_CREATIVE=your_key_here
     - NVIDIA_API_KEY_ANALYTICAL=your_key_here
  3. Run backend: python -m uvicorn main:app --reload --port 8000
  4. Run frontend: npm run dev --port 3000
  5. Test at http://localhost:3000/venues/1/marketing
  6. Open chat, ask a question, verify Supabase logs

